Comment: 0,0:00:03.15,0:00:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was going to frame time this 3 minute special exactly like E-F but there was frame rate differences which made that hard and the timing by E-F was pretty bad. Lines are on for too short a time so I sort of did my own timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.15,0:00:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, Happy New Years!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.86,0:00:07.19,NoteArialEF,,0,0,15,,[note: This episode should be seen\Ninbetween episodes 12 and 13]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.66,0:00:12.30,Sai,,0,0,0,,We received a great deal of positive\Nfeedback from all of you last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:16.43,Sai,,0,0,0,,Please keep watching\NHikaru no Go this year as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.93,0:00:21.74,Sai,,0,0,0,,We would be very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.11,0:00:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sai!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.87,0:00:24.11,Sai,,0,0,0,,Why'd you hit me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking too much for New Years!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.01,0:00:27.75,Sai,,0,0,0,,What!? You've gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.75,0:00:28.75,Background,,0,0,0,,Hikaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.31,0:00:33.95,Background,,0,0,0,,Akari! Wow, that Spring dress looks great on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.49,0:00:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Really Hikaru, what have you been doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.82,0:00:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised that you'd go\Nwith me to greet Yukari-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.99,0:00:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.56,0:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.96,0:00:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Yukari-sensei is in a spring dress too...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.73,0:00:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyways, who's that guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.04,0:00:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about little\Nthings like that on New Years!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on let's go to Yukari-sensei's place, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.31,0:01:01.05,Sai,,0,0,0,,I want to meet Yukari-sensei too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.05,0:01:02.65,NoteArialEF,,0,0,15,,{\fs30\bord1.5\1c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\shad1}Umezawa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.05,0:01:05.45,NoteArialEF,,0,0,15,,{\fs30\bord1.5\1c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\shad1}May I get smarter please.\NMai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.68,0:01:07.05,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord2.5\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HED33EA&\4c&HED33EA&\shad3\move(660,198,470,198)}Mai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.05,0:01:09.52,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord2.5\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HED33EA&\4c&HED33EA&\shad3\pos(470,198)}Mai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.19,0:01:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.29,0:01:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuuki-kun, are you done?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.55,0:01:11.26,Background,,0,0,0,,I'm done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.26,0:01:12.49,NoteArialEF,,0,0,360,,{\fs30\bord1.5\1c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\shad1}To become a Pro.\NYuuki
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.26,0:01:12.49,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HE00009&\4c&HE00009&\shad0\b0\pos(144,278)}Yuuki{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.36,0:01:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's still trying for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.76,0:01:16.73,NoteArialEF,,0,0,15,,[note: Ozouni is a dish made specially on New Years]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.76,0:01:16.33,Background,,0,0,0,,The Ozouni is done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.83,0:01:19.20,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H177AF4&\4c&HE00009&\shad0\b0\move(730,330,300,330)}Teacher Yukari
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:21.27,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H177AF4&\4c&HE00009&\shad0\b0\pos(300,330)}Teacher Yukari
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.20,0:01:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.10,0:01:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, you look great!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.64,0:01:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mai-chan, you look great.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.67,0:01:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, you look better.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.74,0:01:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No Mai-chan, you do.
Comment: 0,0:01:31.91,0:01:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,E-F didn't capitalize this but it should be. Kept as is for now. I think they maybe meant to do , again and not .
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.91,0:01:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No. you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.81,0:01:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mai-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Yuuki-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.85,0:01:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's new years, let's try Uchizome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.72,0:01:42.12,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs38\bord2.5\1c&H3822EC&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\shad0\move(720,289,313,289)}Uchizome
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:43.82,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs38\bord2.5\1c&H3822EC&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\shad0\pos(313,289)}Uchizome
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Uchizome?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Japanese Go Institute, January\NFifth is considered the day of Go, and\Nthey do a Uchizome Ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.39,0:01:50.13,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fs37.5\bord1\1c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\shad2\move(1274.5,295,-309,295)}In the Japanese Go Institute The Uchizome ceremony is held on January Fifth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mai wants to play you, teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.66,0:01:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then I'll play the two of you simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:01:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.54,0:02:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Mai-chan, you place the stones fairly well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.92,0:02:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You took it, Yuuki-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.95,0:02:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy win!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:15.22,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HC9000C&\4c&HC9000C&\shad0\b0\pos(327,308)}Easy win!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.22,0:02:15.85,Default,,0,0,15,,{\an8\fs53\1c&H2CFFF8&)}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.92,0:02:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher, let's draw on the loser's face as a penalty!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.96,0:02:19.69,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HE100D5&\4c&HE100D5&\shad2\pos(325,300)}Let's draw on the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.69,0:02:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs56.5\bord1\1c&H2A81F0&\3c&H92FFFA&\4c&H92FFFA&\shad0\pos(180,315)}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.62,0:02:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the teacher will lose to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.09,0:02:22.33,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HE100D5&\4c&HE100D5&\shad2\pos(328,310)}Maybe the teacher will lose!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.67,0:02:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We resign.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.07,0:02:31.84,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HD10006&\4c&HD10006&\shad0\b0\pos(327,130)}Too bad.
Comment: 0,0:02:31.47,0:02:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,E-F didn't have capital for Hmm but should probably be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.47,0:02:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... you both have much to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.41,0:02:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't want to lose first thing on New Years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.11,0:02:36.54,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord4\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H1E7AF1&\4c&H1E7AF1&\shad0\b0\pos(327,310)}I don't want to lose on New Years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so childish.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.61,0:02:38.74,NoteArialEF,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord2.5\1c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HE100D5&\4c&HE100D5&\shad3\pos(534,10)}New Years\NGreeting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.74,0:02:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.11,0:02:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.32,0:02:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if that's Hikaru-kun.
Comment: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really "blended" so was hard to get an exact match to the timing of E-F. Think it looks ok.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\bord4\i1\1c&HDDDDDD&\move(950,60,-245,60)}New Years Greeting{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.89,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikaru no Go
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.89,0:02:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wishes you a happy new year!
